{"word":"οἰστέος","slug":"οἰστέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἰστέος</b></el> <el>(οἰστέος, η, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:φέρω'><el>φέρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be borne</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>οἰστέον</el> <i>one must bear</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>one must get</i>, <el>κέρδος</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}